Store Configuration Help

\
\
\
\
\ \ \
\
\
\ 1. Limit of products in Up-Sell :\
    \
  1. This is the maximum number of products which you can map to a particular\ product in your Up Sell Page.
    2. \
\
\ 2. Limit of products in Cross-Sell :\
    \
  1. This is the maximum number of products which you can map to a particular\ product in your Cross Sell Page.
    2. \
\
\ 3. Inventory Level for Notification :\
    \
  1. This is the number below which if any of your products go in your shop inventory,\ you will receive a mail notification from our side for replenishment.
    2. \
\
\ 4. Allow Guest Users :\
    \
  1. If this is enabled, the customers will only be asked their email address for fetching\ their respective orders. If disabled, user will be asked their email and password.
    2. \
\
\ 5. Shop Base Currency :\
    \
  1. This is the default base currency of your shop products. This will be the currency\ symbol displayed with all your products on the bot.
    2. \
\
\ 6. Feedback Frequency :\
    \
  1. This is the frequency of how often feedback questions should be asked to the customers.\ You can set these feedback questions in the "Customer Feedback" tab in Product Configuration page.
    2. \
\
\ 7. Reviews & Ratings :\
    \
  1. These fields are for messages which will be shown to customers when asking for a review\ of their previously purchased products.
    2. \
\
\ 8. Display products on landing :\
    \
  1. If enabled, this would show products at the start of the conversation when bot is opened.\ There are 3 possible types of products which can be shown: Latest, Best Selling & Random.
    2. \
\
\ 9. Contact Us Email :\
    \
  1. This is your store support email where the customers can reach out in any kind of difficulty.
    2. \
\
\ 10. Contact Us Phone Number :\
    \
  1. This is your store support contact number where the customers can reach out in any kind of difficulty.
    2. \
\
\ 11. Save :\

  1. On clicking, All information you have entered will get saved.
    2. \
\
\ 12. Mailer Configuration :\

    2. \
\
\ 13. Remove :\
    \
  1. It will remove the Mailer Email address
